Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potatoes{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and halve @button mushrooms{4%oz} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Peel and grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss sweet potato, mushrooms, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, half the @fry seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the remaining Fry Seasoning in the next step.) Roast on middle rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll start the zucchini then).

Meanwhile, toss zucchini on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, remaining @fry seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, and @salt{}. Once veggies have roasted 5 minutes, place sheet with zucchini on top rack. Roast until everything is browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

Rinse @shrimp{10%oz} under cold water; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Open package of shrimp and drain off any excess liquid. Season shrimp all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once pan is hot, add shrimp and cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @honey{2%tsp}, @miso sauce concentrate{1}, a big squeeze of lime juice, and @ginger{}(grated) to taste.

In a separate small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, and a squeeze of lime juice. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Once veggies and zucchini are done, combine on a baking sheet and toss with honey-miso dressing.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{} or #plates{}. Top with sweet potato and mushroom jumble. Drizzle with creamy chili sauce and sprinkle with @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

Top rice with shrimp along with sweet potato and mushroom jumble.